                                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[10 Great Android Apps With Bad Widgets]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/10-great-android-apps-with-bad-widgets/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Jorge A. Aguilar]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/collage-showing-android-widgets-surrounded-by-thumbs-down-icons-and-android-logos.png" length="652" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Android]]></category><category><![CDATA[Apps & Web Apps]]></category><category><![CDATA[Google Calendar]]></category><category><![CDATA[Google]]></category><category><![CDATA[Google Photos]]></category><category><![CDATA[Google Drive]]></category><category><![CDATA[WhatsApp]]></category><category><![CDATA[Snapchat]]></category><category><![CDATA[Gmail]]></category><category><![CDATA[Pokémon GO]]></category><category><![CDATA[Microsoft Outlook]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            Some developers put too little focus on the widget after making great apps.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>Widgets give you a quick look at important information, let you control apps easily, and generally make your Android home screen a much better place. Unfortunately, the reality of Android widgets doesn't always live up to that promise.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Wed, 24 Sep 2025 14:00:14 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/10-great-android-apps-with-bad-widgets/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[This Is Why The iPhone 17 Pro Is Scratching So Much]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/this-is-why-the-iphone-17-pro-is-scratching-so-much/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Arol Wright]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/iphone-17-pro-2.jpeg" length="220" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Iphone]]></category><category><![CDATA[Apple iPhone 17 Pro]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            The return to aluminum unibodies could've gone better.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>Apple's iPhone 17 Pro series marked the company's return to aluminum unibody builds on their phones after around 8 years of continuous glass sandwiches. But it's also a controversial one—it's scratching a little too easily. Thanks to iFixit, we might know the possible reason behind this.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Wed, 24 Sep 2025 13:01:07 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/this-is-why-the-iphone-17-pro-is-scratching-so-much/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[Everything You Need to Know About IT: Welcome to Derry]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/everything-to-know-about-it-welcome-to-derry/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Keeley Brooks]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/it-welcome-to-derry-1.jpg" length="1037" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Streaming]]></category><category><![CDATA[HBO Max]]></category><category><![CDATA[TV Shows]]></category><category><![CDATA[Video Streaming]]></category><category><![CDATA[It: Welcome to Derry]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            Are you ready to go back to the beginning with Pennywise?
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>Stephen King adaptations have always been popular, but it seems that, as of late, we’re seeing more of them grace our screens, and I'm totally cool with that. By the end of 2025, we’ll have seen four films and two shows based on the legendary horror master’s musings—one of those being the highly anticipated <em>IT</em> prequel series, coming soon to <a href="https://www.hbomax.com/" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank">HBO Max</a>.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Wed, 24 Sep 2025 12:15:15 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/everything-to-know-about-it-welcome-to-derry/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[Your Headphones' App Is Good, Actually]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/reasons-you-should-try-your-heaphones-companion-app/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Sydney Butler]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/shutterstock_2470323587.jpg" length="355" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Audio/Video]]></category><category><![CDATA[headphones]]></category><category><![CDATA[Apps & Web Apps]]></category><category><![CDATA[Audio]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            They hide all the good stuff there.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>I'm willing to bet there's a good chunk of people out there who have never installed or used the companion app that goes with their Bluetooth headphones. After all, you don't strictly need to use the app to use the headphones.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Wed, 24 Sep 2025 12:00:16 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/reasons-you-should-try-your-heaphones-companion-app/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[How to Use the chmod Command on Linux]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/437958/how-to-use-the-chmod-command-on-linux/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Dave McKay]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/52865227384_8b80bb45d1_o-1.jpg" length="133" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Linux]]></category><category><![CDATA[Linux & macOS Terminal]]></category><category><![CDATA[Files]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            Learn how Linux file permissions work and how to use the chmod command.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>Control who can access files, search directories, and run scripts using the Linux's <code>chmod</code> command. This command modifies Linux file permissions, which look complicated at first glance but are actually pretty simple once you know how they work.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Wed, 24 Sep 2025 11:30:15 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/437958/how-to-use-the-chmod-command-on-linux/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[The Best Earbuds for iPhone Just Got Even Better]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/the-best-earbuds-for-iphone-just-got-even-better/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Tim Brookes]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2025/09/apple-airpods-pro-3-loose-with-the-case-1.jpg" length="12457" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Audio/Video]]></category><category><![CDATA[Apple AirPods Pro 3]]></category><category><![CDATA[Airpods]]></category><category><![CDATA[headphones]]></category><category><![CDATA[Apple]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            Better in almost every way, Apple only made one questionable change to the AirPods Pro 3.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>With some big design tweaks, bold claims about noise cancellation, and a reputation to uphold, Apple’s <a href="https://www.apple.com/airpods-pro/" target="_blank">AirPods Pro 3</a> have their work cut out. Though they stop short of perfection, I’m relieved to say that Apple has stuck the landing.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Wed, 24 Sep 2025 10:00:15 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/the-best-earbuds-for-iphone-just-got-even-better/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[This Logitech Keyboard Is Powered By Light]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/this-logitech-keyboard-is-powered-by-light/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Arol Wright]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/logitech-light-keyboard-hero.jpg" length="722" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Windows]]></category><category><![CDATA[computer hardware]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            Who needs a cable?
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>There are tons of wireless keyboards out there. But typically, they charge just like everything else does—with a cable. If you want to spin things up a bit, Logitech has the thing for you.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Wed, 24 Sep 2025 07:01:17 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/this-logitech-keyboard-is-powered-by-light/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[LiberNovo’s Record Breaking and Innovative Kickstarter Omni Ergonomic Chair Is Open for Pre-Orders]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/libernovo-innovative-kickstarter-omni-ergonomic-chair/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Sponsored]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/libernovo-omni-chair-used-by-man-working-on-a-computer.png" length="2489" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Promoted]]></category><description><![CDATA[
